main event: A bright orange flame or light was observed from an aircraft at 25,000 feet MSL near San Diego, California on March 12, 1963.
interesting points: The object appeared to make a series of oscillating or side-to-side movements before fading from view.
The observers, Captains T.L. McKeever and R.S. Stuart, were highly reliable R&D project officers with the 8SD (AFSC).
Captain Stuart stated the object indicated a rocket-type engine rather than a jet.
A flight of USAF DAGGER aircraft from a radar facility at Miramar, California reported no unusual sightings in the area.
The report indicates the object was likely a rocket, possibly related to a launch from Vandenberg AFB.
witnesses: Captains T.L. McKeever and R.S. Stuart
